description.narrative: (Tanzania): <!--td {border: 1px solid #ccc;}br {mso-data-placement:same-cell;}-->USDA's Participating Agency Service Agreement (PASA) provides technical assistance and program support to strengthen management capacity for Feed the Future (FTF) programs and to integrate FTF programs with natural resource management activities consistent with U.S Government objectives.FY 2018 FTF funding will provide technical assistance to activities across the Economic Growth Portfolio, including: implementing climate-smart agriculture practices with the Ministry of Agriculture; strengthening the Tanzania Horticulture Association as an industry and the advocacy association for the horticulture sector; staffing expert technical assistance on agriculture and natural resources management; strengthening land management systems through a local organization;providing support for program design, evaluation, and management.This activity's interventions align with the U.S Government priority to create a more sustainable Tanzania by strengthening the country's capacity to deliver services effectively and efficiently in the agriculture sector and adopt and implement policies that will lead to inclusive and market based development while ensuing local organizations have the capacity and management systems necessary to lead development initiatives.
